The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Record 46 Fide-rated players in the fray

A STAFF REPORTER

 Telegraph Schools' Chess 

 Calcutta: The grand finale of The Telegraph Schools Chess Championship kicks off at the Gorky Sadan on Wednesday afternoon with a record 46 Fide-rated players in the fray. 

The total number of entries for the 19th edition of the countrys premier school meet, being organised by Alekhine Chess Club is 328 from 140 schools. Ten states Bihar, Madhya Pradesh, Punjab, Goa, Maharashtra, Karnataka, Jharkhand, Orissa, Assam and Chhattisgarh other than Bengal will be represented. There will also be seven participants from Bangladesh. 

Joining the field will be the top five finishers from the Guwahati, Bhubaneswar and Jamshedpur legs of the meet which took place earlier. 

Two visually challenged players Sudip Rajbanshi amp; Ajahar Alam will vie for honours. So will national under-11 girls champion Rama Kumari of Jamshedpur. 

The tournament, which has produced several top players including Surya Sekhar Ganguly, Sandipan Chanda, Neelotpal Das, Nisha Mohata and Mary Ann Gomes, will be played in the 11-round Swiss League format. The meet will run through January 31, with the prize distribution scheduled for the day after. 

The youngest participants are Mitrabha Guha among boys and Arpita Mukherjee among girls. The champion will take home Rs 15,000 and a trophy. There will be special prizes for different age-groups as well, like all previous years. 




